Gunmen have killed a man and abducted two of his daughters at Azuba in Nasarawa State. The deceased identified as Alhaji Zakari Kigbu is said to be a kinsman of the Nasarawa State Governor, Abdullahi Sule. The Nasarawa State Police Command Spokesman, ASP Ramhan Nansel who confirmed the incident said, “we received a distress call at about 12:15 am about the attack and reacted swiftly by mobilizing our patrol teams and the military to the scene. -Advertisement- “Upon arrival, it was discovered that the victim had been shot on his abdomen. “He was rushed to the hospital where he was confirmed dead.“His two daughters were abducted to an unknown destination. “The command has commenced an intensive manhunt for the perpetrators of the dastardly act.”